==English==
===Etymology===
From Spanish [[desembocar]], from [[des-]] + [[embocar]] ‘run into a creek or strait’, from [[boca]] ‘mouth’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /dɪsɪm'bəʊg/

===Verb===
'''disembogue'''
# to come out into the open [[sea]] from a [[river]] etc
# to pour out, to [[debouch]]

